page_content='21,000 tons of TNT and creating a fireball that measured roughly 2,000 feet in diameter, the first successful test of an atomic bomb, known as the Trinity Test, forever changed the history of the world.","Open today 9:00 a.m. - 5:00 p.m.","945 Magazine Street, New Orleans, LA 70130\ninfo@nationalww2museum.org\n504-528-1944","#1 Attraction\xa0in New Orleans","View Campus Map"}',)'đ̉¸;